Create side-by-side boxplots:

library(tidyr)
NDF <- gather(ages, Gender, Age, -Year)
str(NDF)
Classes 'tbl_df', 'tbl' and 'data.frame':   116 obs. of  3 variables:
 $ Year  : int  1998 1997 1996 1995 1994 1993 1992 1991 1990 1989 ...
 $ Gender: chr  "Women" "Women" "Women" "Women" ...
 $ Age   : num  25 25 24.8 24.5 24.5 24.5 24.4 24.1 23.9 23.8 ...
summary(NDF)
      Year         Gender               Age       
 Min.   :1890   Length:116         Min.   :20.10  
 1st Qu.:1955   Class :character   1st Qu.:21.18  
 Median :1970   Mode  :character   Median :22.95  
 Mean   :1967                      Mean   :23.00  
 3rd Qu.:1984                      3rd Qu.:24.43  
 Max.   :1998                      Max.   :27.10  
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(data = NDF, aes(x = Gender, y = Age, fill = Gender)) + geom_boxplot() + 
  theme_bw()

Changing Colors

ggplot(data = NDF, aes(x = Gender, y = Age, fill = Gender)) + geom_boxplot() + 
  theme_bw() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("blue", "pink"))

Density plots:

ggplot(data = NDF, aes(x = Age, fill = Gender)) + 
  geom_density(alpha = 0.5) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("blue", "pink"))

Summary information:

library(dplyr)
SI <- NDF %>%
  group_by(Gender) %>%
  summarise(av_age = round(mean(Age),2), md_age = round(median(Age),2), sd_age = round(sd(Age),2))
SI
# A tibble: 2  4

Create a time-series plot (see Figure 1):

ggplot(data = ages, aes(x = Year, y = Women)) + 
  geom_line(color = "pink") + 
  geom_point(color = "pink") + 
  geom_smooth(color = "pink") + 
  geom_line(aes(x = Year, y = Men), color = "blue") + 
  geom_point(aes(x = Year, y = Men), color = "blue") + 
  geom_smooth(aes(x = Year, y = Men), color = "blue") +
  labs(y = "Age") +
  theme_bw()

Figure 1: Time Series Plot

Another one using NDF:

ggplot(data = NDF, aes(x = Year, y = Age, color = Gender)) +

  theme_bw() +
